This paper is likely to belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) category as it focuses on the stability issue in training generative adversarial networks (GANs) and proposes optimization methods specifically designed for this adversarial training. The paper also mentions the use of stochastic optimization methods, which are commonly used in machine learning. 

The paper also touches upon mathematical programming and optimization, which suggests that it could also belong to the cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) category. 

Since GANs are commonly used in computer vision applications, the paper could also belong to the cs.CV (Computer Vision) category. 

The paper's focus on improving the training of GANs using optimization methods suggests that it could also belong to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) category. 

Finally, the paper's use of mathematical programming and optimization methods in the context of GANs suggests that it could also belong to the cs.SY (Systems and Control) category.
